      "automation_source": "clawsweeper",
      "repair_reason": "- [P1] The remaining action is current-head Telegram proof, the existing security-fast gate, and maintainer merge handling rather than a narrow automated code repair.; Cleared: Cleared for the diff: it changes Telegram runtime logic and tests only, with no dependency, workflow, secret, or package-resolution changes. (sha=42d60468cda1678f0ec714784fe1c53a0b5ef057)",
      "review_summary": "This PR changes Telegram command-menu sync to store the accepted command set and query `getMyCommands()` for default, `all_group_chats`, and localized variants before using the cached-hash skip, with regression tests.\n\nPR surface: Source +70, Tests +291. Total +361 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-level. Current main can return on a matching process-local Telegram command hash without checking whether Telegram's remote command list is empty; I did not establish a live Telegram reproduction in this read-only review.",
      "review_followup": "- [P1] The remaining action is current-head Telegram proof, the existing `security-fast` gate, and maintainer merge handling rather than a narrow automated code repair.",
